-- design-decisions.md §3's own example shape: recursive occurrence guarded
-- by a Cartesian product. Well-founded (the well-foundedness check accepts
-- it), but recursive-set codegen/solver support isn't implemented yet
-- (docs/recursive-sets-plan.md phases 1-3) — must fail loudly as
-- "not yet supported", not silently compile something wrong.
Tree = Int | Tree * Tree

f : Int -> Int
f(x) = x
